"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-podcasts-2024-8-9-the-take-as-the-paris-olympics-near-the-finish-what-will-we-remember\", \"text\": \"A look at moments of joy and frustration at Paris 2024.  Save  Share  From polluted waters to gender policing - it has been an eventful 2024 Olympics. We jog through the highs and lows as the city starts to lower the Olympic flame.  In this episode:  Episode credits:  This episode was produced by Sar\\u00ed el-Khalili, Ashish Malhotra, Khaled Soltan, and Sonia Bhagat, with Amy Walters, Veronique Eshaya, Duha Mosaad, and me, Malika Bilal.  Our sound designer is Alex Roldan. Alexandra Locke is the Take's Executive Producer, and Ney Alvarez is Al Jazeera's head of audio.  Connect with us:  @AJEPodcasts onTwitter,Instagram,Facebook,ThreadsandYouTube                    Follow Al Jazeera English:\"}"